				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">well its a start.  I would rather have them take small steps and the evaluate the changes instead of making big steps and really hosing everyone over.
<br />

<br />
the bag make sense.. I usually have a big filled with shards anyway.. why not make a bag specific to them and let them stack in that bag only.  and we could have quests to get bigger bags <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" />  I love quests hehe.
<br />

<br />
little fuzzy on how they will implement pvp shards.. but at least they relize it needs to be done.  I still find it odd that we are the only class really that has a restriction of regeants for our spells but we get no real benefit from them.. they are spells we need to function properly haha.  the only real argument is the healthstone.. and that I would say is needed by most warlocks because we wear the cloths, and the only way we can get a shield like some other classes is to have a specific pet up.  and people just keep running at us with pointy things!  
<br />

<br />
I am pleased so far.. lets see what happens.  alot of classes need to be -fixed-  (I didn't say nerfed haha)... I cant wait until they fix seal of the crusader im tired of a class, that people keep saying isn't a damage dealing class, hitting me for 500 and then doing an almost full heal with an insanely small amount of mana.  a priest and I drained one yesterday and he had the tiniest bit left and BLAMMO.. 'hey im full health again suckers!' haha.  oh well.. we just drowned him <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />  I hear rogues have issues too, but I just don't care.  rogue are tha debil!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=849817" target="_blank" class="postlink">Aithur the Enchanter (69)</a> [<span style="color: blue">Retired</span>]
