			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Soul-shard only bags are tricky because if Blizz implements them, they're essentially saying "hey, THIS is the appropriate number of soul shards to carry - fill up the bag!" to the Warlock community. It will be maximally efficient (assuming the soulshard bag holds a reasonable amount) to have one soul shard bag and to carry exactly enough shards to fill it.
<br />

<br />
That sort of contradicts the fact that:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">e want players to strategically manage the number of shards they carry at a given time.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
So it's a bit more complicated than that.
<br />

<br />
I think it'd be nice to make a quest for a Reagent Conservation (ala EQ) sort of augment for Soul Shards. It could start by giving warlocks a 5% (or whatever) chance to save a shard on any given cast of a spell and scale up from there on more powerful versions. They can implement it as a quest <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />.
<br />

<br />
That takes some of the pressure off of warlocks but still keeps the need to manage shards.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
