			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You know, the whole soul shard issue really doesn't bother me much any more. I've kind of gotten used to it. I "strategically manage" my shards by:
<br />

<br />
1) Not PvP'ing with my warlock
<br />

<br />
and
<br />

<br />
2) Not helping lower level people with my warlock. (Or if I do, not using any abilities that require shards.)
<br />

<br />
As long as I avoid those, about the only time I run low on shards is if I end up summoning a bunch of people and handing out healthstones and then not killing a bunch of mobs. It happens (group breaks up, or just got together to kill one big mob) but it's rare.
<br />

<br />
Raids may be another matter--not there yet.
<br />

<br />
So if that was the intention of shards, I'd say they're quite successful. Other than that, they don't limit me at all. I use shard-based abilities at will, limited only by timers, mana, etc. because I can easily get more than I can use when fighting mobs near my level.
<br />

<br />
Dropping the requirement for shards completely would have a minimal impact on most warlock abilities, but don't hold your breath.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
